            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1961-02-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1961-02-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="187"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d187">
                <head>187. National Security Action Memorandum No. 16<note n="0" type="source"
                        xml:id="d187fn0">Source: Department of State, <gloss target="#t_SS1"
                            >S/S</gloss>-<gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Files: Lot 72 D 316,
                            <gloss target="#t_NSAM1">NSAM</gloss>s, <gloss target="#t_NSAM1"
                            >NSAM</gloss> 16. Top Secret.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1961-02-13">February 13, 1961</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="to">
                    <head>TO</head>
                    <item>The Secretary of State</item>
                </list>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Economic Support for Newly-Independent Areas</item>
                </list>
                <p>The record of action of the <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> meeting of
                    February 9, 1961<note n="1" xml:id="d187fn1">A record of the February 9 meeting
                        of the National Security Council is in the <persName corresp="#p_KJF2"
                            >Kennedy</persName> Library, National Security Files, Meetings and
                        Memoranda Series, <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Meeting No. 476. The
                        subject of <gloss target="#t_NSAM1">NSAM</gloss> No. 16 was covered by
                            <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Record of Action No. 2404-b.</note>
                    shows in Paragraph 3. b. that the President has approved revision of <gloss
                        target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> policies along the lines recommended by the
                    Secretary of State to provide flexibility for the United States to supplement
                    Western European support to newly-independent areas whenever such action is in
                    the United States interest. In my judgment, this action constitutes a revision
                    of the applicable policies, but if new language is desired in all the
                    appropriate documents, we will expect to receive it from the Department of
                    State.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BMG2">
                            <hi rend="strong">McGeorge Bundy</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
